{
  "text": "In the approach of Donnachie and Landshoff, a Pomeron is viewed as a vector object [2] . However, as was discussed in [CITATION_1] , such an approach gives a negative x-s value. It is also possible to define it as a scalar or a rank-2 tensor object [CITATION_2] . As was shown in [CITATION_3] , the STAR data [CITATION_4] prefer the tensor over the scalar Pomeron model.",
  "citation_candidates": [
